abstracts.cdata!:
Ratings for the Third Social Fund for
            Egypt were as follows: the outcome was satisfactory, risk to
            development outcome moderate, and the Bank and Borrower
            performance were both moderately satisfactory. Lessons
            learned from the project: there is a need to set out a
            hierarchy between project objectives; quality at entry can
            be compromised when projects are prepared on a fast track
            basis; Institutional issues such as monitoring and
            evaluation and targeting need to be dealt with up front
            during project preparation; and field presence can enhance
            supervision effectiveness.

repnme.cdata!: Egypt - Third Social Fund for Development Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The Third Social Fund for Development
            Project's objective is to help create jobs and provide
            community infrastructure and services through labor
            intensive works. The project consists of two components. 1)
            Public works program funds small-scale public works programs
            in partnership with communities and local government, which
            are executed by small local private contractors. Projects
            funded include construction, rehabilitation and repair of
            irrigation and drainage canals, water supply and sewerage
            systems, rural roads and streets, and public buildings.
            Maintenance include canal cleaning, public buildings, and
            solid waste collection and disposal. 2) Community
            development program will support the development of
            community support infrastructure and services, in
            partnership with local groups, to reduce poverty and improve
            the quality of life, and to promote community and
            nongovernmental organization participation.
